We shall always have the breast swim and may it reign for a long time.
But if I may modestly make arguments for my particular favorite, then let me draw attention to the discreet charm of the trampoline.
Although trampoline jumping has been an Olympic event since 2000, when it debuted in Sydney, it's been so underreported for the last 16 years that many of those I've interviewed didn't even know it was an Olympic sport.
It could be regional ignorance.
Although the United States sent athletes to the competition, it has never won a medal in trampolining and until 2012 had no athlete who made it to the final round.
The Chinese and the Russians tend to share the prices for the men and the Chinese and the Canadians for the women.
