The built-in memory was originally eight megabytes, which would be enough for about two high-resolution selfies today.
An iPhone now comes with at least 16 gigabytes.
The Nokia 9000 Communicator came to market exactly 20 years ago, on August 15, 1996, and it was the world's first smartphone.
