Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec is close to reaching turnover of 1 billion
High demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted Carl Zeiss Meditec's sales.
In the first nine months of the financial year, which began in October, group sales rose by 6.7 percent to €798.6 million, the listed company announced on Friday in Jena.
The Asian business grew disproportionately, by 17.1 percent.
Profit before interest and taxes increased from EUR 89.5 million to EUR 110.5 million, according to the interim balance sheet.
The Jena-based medical technology group aims to surpass the 1 billion euro turnover mark this financial year, the board confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment and appliances for doctors' offices and clinics.
The company, which is part of the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs nearly 3000 people.
